### Steps to Enroll and Switch Plans in Sugar Land, Texas

You cannot switch plans whenever you want. Medicare enrollment into a Medicare Advantage plan usually happens during set election windows, including your initial enrollment period, the annual open enrollment period from October 15 through December 7, and certain situations that qualify for a special enrollment period, demonstrating eligibility for medicaid services.

To enroll or switch plans, you can:

- Complete and sign an election form from the plan.
- Use another CMS-approved enrollment method offered by the plan.
- Call 1-800-MEDICARE or contact the plan directly.

If you want to leave a plan, timing still matters. In many cases, your new coverage or disenrollment becomes effective on the first day of the following month. Some people qualify for extra flexibility, including those who move, lose plan coverage, live in an institution, or meet other special enrollment period rules. Always confirm deadlines before you switch plans.

